- `evalDist select` is the distribution corresponding to picking an element
  uniformly at random from `α`.
- The support of `select` is the entire type `α`.
- The probability of any element `a` under `select` is `1 / (card α)` if `α` is finite, and
  some positive value if `α` is infinite (though we mostly care about finite types).
- The failure probability of `select` is 0.

This definition is still somewhat informal. The main idea is that `α` has a " canonical" way
to pick an element uniformly at random.

