  -- x : α × β
  -- y : α × β
  -- We need to show that Pr[=x | (·, ·) <$> Sα <*> Sβ] = Pr[=y | (·, ·) <$> Sα <*> Sβ]
  -- where Sα is the sampleable type for α and Sβ is the sampleable type for β
  -- Let's compute the probability for a generic pair (a,b)
  -- Pr[=(a,b) | Sα <*> Sβ] = Pr[=a | Sα] * Pr[=b | Sβ]
  -- By definition of sampleable type for α and β
  -- Pr[=a | Sα] = 1 / card α
  -- Pr[=b | Sβ] = 1 / card β
  -- Therefore, Pr[=(a,b) | Sα <*> Sβ] = (1 / card α) * (1 / card β)
  -- This probability is the same for any pair (a,b)
  -- Therefore, the probability of selecting x is the same as the probability of selecting y
